---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy — TextWizard';
const description =
  "TextWizard's privacy policy. Everything runs in your browser — we don't collect or store your text. Hosting is Cloudflare; analytics is cookieless, self-hosted Plausible.";
---
<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <main class="container legal">
    <p><a href="/" class="legal-back">← Back to TextWizard</a></p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: 2026-07-16</p>

    <h2>The short version</h2>
    <p>
      TextWizard runs entirely in your browser. The text you type or paste is
      <strong>never sent to a server</strong> — it lives only in your browser's local
      storage so your work persists between visits. There are no user accounts, no logins,
      and no tracking of what you actually transform with the tools.
    </p>

    <h2>Data we (and our providers) handle</h2>

    <h3>1. Hosting — Cloudflare</h3>
    <p>
      This site is served by Cloudflare. When you visit any page, Cloudflare receives
      standard web request metadata (your IP address, browser user-agent, requested URL,
      timestamp) to deliver the page and protect against abuse. We don't access these logs
      directly; they are governed by
      <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Traffic measurement — Plausible Analytics</h3>
    <p>
      We use <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy-focused-web-analytics" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Plausible Analytics</a>,
      a privacy-friendly, <strong>cookieless</strong> analytics tool that we <strong>self-host</strong>.
      It counts page views and basic, aggregate visit metadata (such as referrer, and rough
      device/country derived from your IP) so we can understand which tools are used. It
      <strong>does not use cookies</strong>, does not create persistent identifiers, does not
      track you across sites, and does not collect any personal data. Your IP address is used
      only transiently to generate aggregate counts and is never stored against you. We never
      see the content of your textarea — only that a page was viewed.
    </p>

    <h3>3. Browser local storage</h3>
    <p>
      TextWizard saves a few things in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> so the app
      works the way you'd expect:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>The current text in each tool's textarea (so it survives reloads).</li>
      <li>Your light/dark theme choice.</li>
      <li>Your last-used filename and extension when saving.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This data <strong>never leaves your device</strong>. You can clear it anytime via your
      browser's site-data controls, or with the <em>Clear</em> button on each tool.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We don't have user accounts or logins.</li>
      <li>We don't send your text or files to any server.</li>
      <li>We don't sell, share, or rent any data.</li>
      <li>We don't set advertising cookies, retargeting pixels, or fingerprinting.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      TextWizard sets <strong>no cookies</strong>. Our analytics (Plausible) is cookieless.
      Cloudflare may set a security cookie (<code>__cf_bm</code>) to distinguish humans from
      bots as part of serving and protecting the site.
    </p>

    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      TextWizard is a general-purpose utility and is not directed at children under 13. We do
      not knowingly collect personal information from children.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If this policy changes, the "Last updated" date at the top will change and the revised
      policy will be posted at this URL.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions or concerns? Open an issue at
      <a href="https://github.com/MichalAFerber/textwizard/issues" rel="noopener" target="_blank">github.com/MichalAFerber/textwizard</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>
